<sub>0</sub> by the mean and variance of the distribution. Denoting the variance by <italic>λ</italic> and using as the mean the reference mapping bias <italic>μ</italic>∈(0,1), as discussed above, we get: 
<disp-formula id="Equ5"><label>5</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M13">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
